7 An Act relating to medical marijuana; requiring the
display of certain signage in dispensaries and
8 businesses; providing contents and requirements of
sign; requiring owners pay cost of signs; providing
9 for codification; and providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 427.30 of Title 63, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. Every medical marijuana dispensary or any place medical
17 marijuana or tetrahydrocannabinol (THC) products are sold shall post
18 and display at all times a printed sign, with a minimum height of
19 eight and one-half (8 1/2) inches and a minimum width of eleven (11)
20 inches with a font size of no less than 48 points for the text, near
21 the cash register or place of checkout and at least two other highly
22 visible places in the store, which shall read as follows:
23 WARNING: INGESTING THC PRODUCTS WHILE PREGNANT IS NOT HEALTHY
24 FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF AN UNBORN CHILD.
